{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":27988,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-02-06T02:10:10.125Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eLoosely inspired by the Unity-chan shaders with a few extra niceties like MSDF \u003cem\u003eink lines\u003c/em\u003e and geometry-shader outline emission.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/4/4414709fc432634a44aac8b8d76a419eab0021cf.jpeg\" alt=\"Blocks_2019-02-05_16-40-15\" width=\"406\" height=\"349\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAbove: MSDF for the black lines inside, 3 step tone-map, white rim-highlight, and GS-emitted outline.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRequirements\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eColormap (texture 0)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eToneMap (texture 7)\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003econtrols the shade falloff\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eleftmost is perpendicular, rightmost is aligned to the light direction\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOptions\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHair highlight ring (cylindrical matcap basically)\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etex 4\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMatcap / Spherical environment map\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etex 4\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRim highlight (TOON_RIMLIGHT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMSDF Linework map for sharp sketch lines (TOON_LINE_MAP)\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etex 5\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eControl map (force light/dark)\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etex 3\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eR\u003c/strong\u003e: min allowed shade, \u003cstrong\u003eG\u003c/strong\u003e: max allowed shade, \u003cstrong\u003eB\u003c/strong\u003e: unused, \u003cstrong\u003eA\u003c/strong\u003e: matcap mask\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVertical shade map\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eClips maximum possible lighting, like the control map can\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNx1 texture is silly quick to update at runtime for changes (hat shadow, etc)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eprovide size coordinates for normalization to \u003ccode\u003eVerticalRampShift\u003c/code\u003e parameter\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSpecular is used as per legacy pipeline\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003enot toon clipped in any way, it’s \u003cem\u003especial\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eToon.hlsl\u003c/code\u003e contains documentation at the top.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOutlines\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGeometry shader outlines included (if you have GS support)\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eemits flipped winding triangles\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003eToon_Outline.hlsl\u003c/code\u003e can be used in an additional render-path pass (with the culling flipped) to do outlines with the same config\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003eOutlinePower\u003c/code\u003e: \u003cstrong\u003ex\u003c/strong\u003e = offset along normal, \u003cstrong\u003ey\u003c/strong\u003e = offset along view-vector\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://gist.github.com/JSandusky/4f9a4f00110691eb45104f69abd32f75\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://gist.github.com/JSandusky/4f9a4f00110691eb45104f69abd32f75\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShouldn’t be too much cruft in there. Tessellation (lots of code no one can use) and light-prepass stripped out (not for stock prepass, would be confusing to look at).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’ll probably port to GLES3 and GL3.1 (interface blocks)\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-02-06T02:10:10.125Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":817,"reads":53,"readers_count":52,"score":4125.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":4898,"topic_slug":"toon-shader-hlsl","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://gist.github.com/JSandusky/4f9a4f00110691eb45104f69abd32f75","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"HLSL Toon Shader · GitHub","clicks":124}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":27989,"name":"","username":"I3DB","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/i/3ec8ea/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-02-06T02:31:10.504Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eDo you have a material that uses this you could share?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOr a simple working sample.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-02-06T02:31:10.504Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":29.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":4898,"topic_slug":"toon-shader-hlsl","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1086,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":27990,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-02-06T02:49:22.032Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHere’s the technique I start with when fiddling with it:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;technique vs=\"Toon\" ps=\"Toon\" psdefines=\"TOON_LINE_MAP\" vsdefines=\"\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"outline\" vs=\"Toon_Outline\" ps=\"Toon_Outline\" cull=\"cw\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"light\" depthtest=\"equal\" depthwrite=\"false\" blend=\"add\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"depth\" vs=\"Depth\" ps=\"Depth\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"shadow\" vs=\"Shadow\" ps=\"Shadow\" /\u0026gt;\n    \n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"0\" name=\"Color\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"1\" name=\"Normal Map\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"2\" name=\"Specular Map\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"3\" name=\"Control Map\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"4\" name=\"MatCap / Hair-Ring\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"5\" name=\"Linework\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"6\" name=\"Vertical Shade\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;alias unit=\"7\" name=\"Tone Map\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/technique\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI plan to put together a sample scene but I need to write an appropriate environment toon-shader to go with all of this. This shader isn’t particularly great for anything that isn’t a first-class object (ie. saturation and extinction/inscattering for that cartoon background fade, etc). Probably have one ready by the weekend.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe alias tags up there are for my editor, left them there though because they do a good job of indicating what different samplers do.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMSDFs for the line maps have been generated with \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/Chlumsky/msdfgen\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/Chlumsky/msdfgen\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-02-06T02:49:22.032Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":69.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":4898,"topic_slug":"toon-shader-hlsl","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Chlumsky/msdfgen","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - Chlumsky/msdfgen: Multi-channel signed distance field generator","clicks":23}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[27988,27989,27990]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,1386]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7110,"title":"Resource fetch define","fancy_title":"Resource fetch define","slug":"resource-fetch-define","posts_count":2,"reply_count":0,"highest_post_number":2,"image_url":null,"created_at":"2021-12-27T12:28:55.126Z","last_posted_at":"2021-12-27T17:00:37.699Z","bumped":true,"bumped_at":"2021-12-27T17:00:37.699Z","archetype":"regular","unseen":false,"pinned":false,"unpinned":null,"visible":true,"closed":false,"archived":false,"boo